{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DjaHa7MXXqBLZ8ii6vUGZy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the source file and convert it to a knowledge file following the work steps.\n\n**Work Step 1: Identify the title**\nThe first heading underlined with `=====` is \"内部フォーワードハンドラ\"\n\n**Work Step 1.5: Check for no-knowledge-content source**\nThe source contains Layer A and Layer B content (handler descriptions, processing flow, configuration examples), so `no_knowledge_content: false`.\n\n**Work Step 2: Build the section list**\nRST h2 sections (underlined with `-----`):\n1. 概要 (Overview)\n2. ハンドラ処理フロー (Handler Processing Flow)\n\n\n3. 設定項目・拡張ポイント (Configuration Items)\n\nNow I'm estimating the character counts for each section to determine if any need h3 promotion. The overview section covers handler descriptions and related concepts, the processing flow section details the numbered steps, and the configuration section is quite brief with just XML examples. All three sections appear to be under 2000 characters, so they'll remain as h2 sections without further subdivision.\n\nFor the first section, I'm extracting the key details about ForwardingHandler—it re-executes subsequent handlers when the response content path starts with `forward://`, handles internal forwarding for screens with business action processing, and updates the request path and thread context ID after forwarding.\n\nFor the second section, I'm noting that the forwarded request ID comes from the internal request ID reference, and this handler needs to be positioned above ServiceAvailabilityCheckHandler and PermissionCheckHandler since those checks run against the forwarded request ID. The handler flow shows that on inbound it creates a shallow copy of the handler queue and delegates to subsequent handlers to get the HTTP response, while on outbound it appears to be handling the response content path check.\n\nNow I'm looking at the forwarding logic: if the content path starts with `forward://`, it triggers internal forwarding with the format `forward://(destination request path)` supporting both relative and absolute paths. The forwarding process involves setting the request path, updating the internal request ID, replacing the handler queue with its copy for re-execution, comparing status codes and keeping the larger one, then returning the response. Error handling for subsequent handlers is also part of this flow.\n\nFor configuration, the ForwardingHandler requires no additional settings and can be used as-is with the XML component declaration. There are also cross-references to the request object, internal request ID, and related handlers like ServiceAvailabilityCheckHandler and PermissionCheckHandler.\n\nLooking at the official documentation URLs, the base URL is empty, so there are no external documentation references to include.\n\nNow I'm structuring the JSON output. For the overview section, the key details are the ForwardingHandler class from nablarch.fw.handler, which intercepts HTTP responses with content paths starting with `forward://` and re-executes subsequent handlers with the specified request path for internal forwarding.\n\nThe important points are that the request path gets rewritten to the forwarding destination, the thread context request ID remains unchanged after forwarding, and the forwarded request ID is accessible through the internal request ID reference. Since the availability and permission checks use the forwarded request ID, this handler needs to be positioned above those handlers in the chain.\n\nFor the handler processing flow section, I'm laying out the numbered steps that describe how the handler processes requests.\n\nFor configuration, there are no configuration items needed, just an XML example showing how to set this up.\n\nNow I'm documenting the `ForwardingHandler` class, which intercepts HTTP responses with `forward://` paths and re-executes the subsequent handler chain at the specified request path for internal forwarding. This is useful when the destination screen involves business action processing. After forwarding, the request path in the request object gets replaced with the forward destination, the thread context request ID stays the same, but the forwarded request ID can be accessed through the internal request ID reference. It's important to place this handler above `ServiceAvailabilityCheckHandler` and `PermissionCheckHandler` since those need to perform their checks using the forwarded request ID.\n\nNow I'm outlining the forward processing flow, starting with creating a shallow copy of the handler queue and then handling the subsequent handlers... ドラに処理を委譲し、HTTPレスポンスオブジェクトを取得する\n\n**[復路処理]**\n\n3. HTTPレスポンスオブジェクトのコンテンツパスを確認して、`forward://` で始まらない場合はそのまま結果を返す。`forward://` で始まる場合は内部フォーワード処理を実行し、フォーワード先のリクエストパスを設定してリクエストIDをスレッドコンテキストに反映させ、ハンドラキューのコピーを使って後続ハンドラを再実行する。初回レスポンスのステータスコードが再実行時より大きければそれを保持する。\n\n後続ハンドラ処理中に例外が発生した場合はそのまま再送出する。\n\n設定項目はなく、コンポーネント定義で直接使用できる。 When the HTTP response content path starts with `forward://`, the handler re-executes subsequent handlers with the specified request path for an internal forward operation, which is useful when the destination screen involves business action processing. The request path in the request object gets rewritten to the forward destination, the thread context request ID remains unchanged, and the forwarded request gets assigned an internal request ID.\n\nSince the ServiceAvailabilityCheckHandler and PermissionCheckHandler need to perform their checks using the forwarded request ID, this handler must be positioned above those handlers in the chain.\n\nThe processing flow involves creating a shallow copy of the handler queue, delegating to subsequent handlers to obtain the HTTP response object, then examining that response object during the return path.\n\nNow I'm checking the response content path to determine whether to proceed with an internal forward operation—if it starts with `forward://`, I parse the target request path which can be specified as either a relative path from the current request URI or an absolute path from the servlet context root.\n\nWhen an internal forward is needed, I update the request path in the HttpRequest object, set the forward request ID in the thread context, replace the handler queue with a copy from the initial request, and re-execute the subsequent handlers to get a new response, then compare status codes to determine which response to use.\n\nFor exception handling, any errors that occur during the re-execution of handlers are simply re-thrown. The component itself requires no configuration and can be used as-is with just the basic XML declaration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21730,"cache_read_input_tokens":29889,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21730,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fb75b8b6-4c40-4a2a-ae36-60fee800e55f","uuid":"ea8027e1-39f8-41b2-9d73-e0cf104c15de"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DjaHa7MXXqBLZ8ii6vUGZy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01K5QbYRDmz8FjpdDyB5nn3r","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"id":"handlers-ForwardingHandler","title":"内部フォーワードハンドラ","no_knowledge_content":false,"official_doc_urls":[],"index":[{"id":"s1","title":"概要","hints":["ForwardingHandler","nablarch.fw.handler.ForwardingHandler","内部フォーワード","forward://","ServiceAvailabilityCheckHandler","PermissionCheckHandler","内部リクエストID","コンテンツパス"]},{"id":"s2","title":"ハンドラ処理フロー","hints":["ForwardingHandler","内部フォーワード処理","forward://","コンテンツパス","ハンドラキュー","HttpRequest","ステータスコード","往路処理","復路処理"]},{"id":"s3","title":"設定項目・拡張ポイント","hints":["ForwardingHandler","nablarch.fw.web.handler.ForwardingHandler","設定項目なし","コンポーネント設定"]}],"sections":{"s1":"**クラス名**: `nablarch.fw.handler.ForwardingHandler`\n\nHTTPレスポンスのコンテンツパスが `forward://` で始まる場合、指定されたリクエストパスで後続ハンドラの処理を再実行する（内部フォーワード）。遷移先画面が業務アクション処理を伴う場合などに用いる。\n\n- フォーワード後: :ref:`リクエストオブジェクト<request_processing>` 中のリクエストパスはフォーワード先に書き換えられる\n- スレッドコンテキストのリクエストIDはフォーワード後も同じ値のまま変わらない\n- フォーワード先のリクエストIDは :ref:`内部リクエストID<internal_request_id>` から参照可能\n\n> **重要**: :doc:`ServiceAvailabilityCheckHandler`、:doc:`PermissionCheckHandler` の開閉局チェック・認可チェックはフォーワード後のリクエストIDで実施する必要があるため、本ハンドラはこれらの上位に配置すること。","s2":"**[往路処理]**\n\n1. ハンドラキュー構成のシャローコピーを作成する\n2. 後続ハンドラに処理を委譲し、HTTPレスポンスオブジェクトを取得する\n\n**[復路処理]**\n\n3. HTTPレスポンスオブジェクトのコンテンツパスを取得する\n   - `forward://` で始まらない場合: 処理結果をそのままリターンして終了\n   - `forward://` で始まる場合（内部フォーワード処理）:\n     - 書式: `forward://(フォーワード先リクエストパス)`\n       - 相対パス指定: 現在のリクエストURIを起点とするパス\n       - 絶対パス指定: サーブレットコンテキスト名を起点とするパス\n     ```bash\n     # 現在のリクエストURIが \"/app/user/success.html\" の場合、以下は等価\n     forward://registerForm.html            # 相対パス指定\n     forward:///app/user/registerForm.html  # 絶対パス指定\n     ```\n     - 処理手順:\n       1. フォーワード先リクエストパスを `HttpRequest` オブジェクトのリクエストパスに設定\n       2. フォーワード先リクエストIDをスレッドコンテキスト上の :ref:`内部リクエストID<internal_request_id>` に設定\n       3. ハンドラキューの内容を往路で作成したコピーに差し替えたうえで後続ハンドラを再実行し、HTTPレスポンスオブジェクトを取得\n       4. 初回レスポンスのステータスコードが再実行レスポンスのステータスコードより大きい場合、再実行レスポンスにその値を設定\n       5. 再実行レスポンスをリターンして終了\n\n**[例外処理]**\n\n後続ハンドラ処理中のエラーはそのまま再送出して終了する。","s3":"設定項目はなく、そのまま使用可能。\n\n```xml\n<component class=\"nablarch.fw.web.handler.ForwardingHandler\" />\n```"}}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21730,"cache_read_input_tokens":29889,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21730,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fb75b8b6-4c40-4a2a-ae36-60fee800e55f","uuid":"a82ac9d0-fabe-407c-b40c-cb8c4613675d"}
